Second Quarter 2017 Highlights

    1. The tonnage processed increased by 20% due to circuits #2 and #3 being
       used exclusively for the processing of the Avino mine material.  The mill
       availability rate increased by 13% over the second quarter of 2016 during
       which time there were mechanical issues with the ball mill of circuit #3.
       In the second quarter we opted to mine by slashing the vein to provide
       mill feed, therefore the mine development decreased by 38%.
    2. Silver and gold feed grades increased by 19% and 106% respectively while
       the copper grade decreased by 10% due to the change in mineralization.
    3. Gold recovery improved by 14% due to the higher feed grade realized,
       while the silver and copper recoveries remained stable with minor changes
       seen.
    4. The higher tonnage processed resulted in 18% more concentrate produced
       although the copper feed grade decreased by 9%.
    5. Gold production increased by 181%, while silver and copper increased by
       43% and 7% respectively.
    6. The higher tonnage processed, together with the higher silver and feed
       grades resulted in 50% more silver equivalent ounces produced.


San Gonzalo Mine Second Quarter 2017 Production Highlights
Comparative figures for the second quarter 2017 and the second quarter 2016 for the San Gonzalo mine are as follows:


                                                      Q2         Q2         Quarterly            YTD          Notes
                                                            2017       2016                             2017
